# Core AI Coding Rules

- Read relevant files before editing.
- Make the smallest possible change.
- Do not modify unrelated files.
- Do not refactor unless explicitly requested.
- Do not rewrite entire files for small changes.
- Do not add new abstractions unless there is a concrete need.
- Do not add new dependencies unless necessary and explain why.
- Preserve existing comments, formatting, imports, and file structure unless the task requires changes.
- Before implementing, inspect 3-5 relevant files and follow existing project patterns.
- Prefer existing components, hooks, utilities, and types over creating new ones.
- After changes, summarize changed files, behavior changes, and risks.
